{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "The experiment on searching for \u03b7-mesic 3 He nucleus was performed in May 2014 at COSY accelerator in Juelich by WASA-at-COSY Collaboration. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The measurements were carried out using ramped beam technique which allows for the slow and continuous beam momentum change near the threshold of \u03b7 meson creation. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The luminosity was obtained based on pd \u2192 3 He\u03b7 reaction and quasielastic proton-proton scattering. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The bound state of \u03b7-meson and 3 He nucleus is searched for in pd \u2192 3 He2\u03b3 and pd \u2192 3 He6\u03b3 channels. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The analysis is still in progress and the estimated upper limit value is on the level of few nanobarns.",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Introduction",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The \u03b7-mesic nuclei were postulated more than 30 years ago [1] and currently are one of the hottest topic in nuclear physics from experimental and theoretical point of view [2][3][4][5][6]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 58,
                    "end": 61,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 172,
                    "end": 175,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 175,
                    "end": 178,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 178,
                    "end": 181,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "[4]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 181,
                    "end": 184,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[5]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 184,
                    "end": 187,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "[6]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The experimental searches for \u03b7-mesic helium-3 have been performed by MAMI [7,8] and COSY11 [9,10] collaborations but no bound state was observed. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 75,
                    "end": 78,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "[7,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 78,
                    "end": 80,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "8]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 92,
                    "end": 95,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "[9,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 95,
                    "end": 98,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "10]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 70,
                    "end": 75,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MAMI",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In the experiment studying \u03b7 meson photoproduction [7,8], a peak-like structure was observed though its interpretation is still a subject of discussion. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 51,
                    "end": 54,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "[7,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 54,
                    "end": 56,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "8]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In earlier experiments on hadronic \u03b7 production [9,10], the upper limit for bound state creation cross section upper 70 nb was obtained.",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 48,
                    "end": 51,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "[9,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 51,
                    "end": 54,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "10]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Earlier, WASA-at-COSY collaboration has performed measurements in order to search for \u03b7 mesic 4 He nucleus [11][12][13][14] and no bound state was observed. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 94,
                    "end": 95,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "4"
                },
                {
                    "start": 107,
                    "end": 111,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b10",
                    "text": "[11]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 111,
                    "end": 115,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b11",
                    "text": "[12]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 115,
                    "end": 119,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b12",
                    "text": "[13]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 119,
                    "end": 123,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b13",
                    "text": "[14]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In current experiment [15], the statistics gathered is the largest one ever obtained for this experimental conditions. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 22,
                    "end": 26,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b14",
                    "text": "[15]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The expected result accuracy is of few nanobarns order of magnitude. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "In case if the bound state is observed, the width is expected to be larger then the binding energy [16].",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 99,
                    "end": 103,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b15",
                    "text": "[16]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Luminosity estimation",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "One of the most important questions in current experiment is data normalization. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "For this purpose we obtain luminosity analyzing reactions that have known cross sections. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The luminosity as a function of the beam momentum is needed. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "This dependence can be essential because of small beam trajectory changes during each accelerator cycle that can influence the target overlapping [17]. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 146,
                    "end": 150,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b16",
                    "text": "[17]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Luminosity estimation is based on pd \u2192 3 He\u03b7 and pd \u2192 ppn spectator reactions [18,19].",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 78,
                    "end": 82,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b17",
                    "text": "[18,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 82,
                    "end": 85,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b18",
                    "text": "19]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The registration efficiencies have been obtained from Monte Carlo simulations. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "For pd \u2192 3 He\u03b7 reaction simulation, the cross sections and angular distributions have been taken * e-mail: alexrndl@gmail.com , 0",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "(201 E Web of Conferences https://doi.org/10.1051/e onf /201919902029 PJ pjc 199 20 9) ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 81,
                    "end": 83,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b19",
                    "text": "20"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "MESON 2018 29 from references [20,23]. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 30,
                    "end": 34,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b19",
                    "text": "[20,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 34,
                    "end": 37,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b22",
                    "text": "23]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "For quasielastic proton-proton scattering, the simulation was performed in the frame of spectator model analogously as in analysis described in ref. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "[21,22]. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 4,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b20",
                    "text": "[21,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 4,
                    "end": 7,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b21",
                    "text": "22]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The distribution of Fermi motion momentum for nucleons in target deuteron was calculated using PARIS model [24] while the proton-proton scattering cross sections were taken from SAID database [25]. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 107,
                    "end": 111,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b23",
                    "text": "[24]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 192,
                    "end": 196,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b24",
                    "text": "[25]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The obtained quasielastic scattering cross section was multiplied by a factor of 0.955 taking into account the shading effect [26].",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 126,
                    "end": 130,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b25",
                    "text": "[26]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The events from pd \u2192 3 He\u03b7 and pd \u2192 ppn spectator reactions are identified by algorithms that were applied for raw data and Monte Carlo simulation results in order to obtain the number of experimental of events and to calculate the efficiency. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The integrated luminosity in this experiment is calculated by the formula",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "where N data and N MC are the number of events extracted from data and Monte Carlo simulation correspondingly, \u03c3 is the reaction's cross section, and is the efficiency. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "S trigger is the trigger's scaling factor set up during the measurements. ",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "S MC is the total number of generated Monte Carlo events.",
            "section": "Luminosity estimation",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Searching for a bound state",
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The pd \u2192 3 He\u03b3\u03b3 and pd \u2192 3 He6\u03b3 channels are investigated to search for 3 He \u2212 \u03b7 bound state. ",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 72,
                    "end": 73,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In these channels, the bound state would be visible in case of direct bound \u03b7 decay without being absorbed by any nucleon: pd \u2192 ( 3 He\u03b7) bound \u2192 3 He\u03b3\u03b3 and pd \u2192 ( 3 He\u03b7) bound \u2192 3 He\u03c0 0 \u03c0 0 \u03c0 0 \u2192 3 He6\u03b3. ",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "For efficiency estimation, the Monte Carlo simulation for bound state production and decay was performed. ",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The distribution of 3 He \u2212 \u03b7 relative momentum was calculated by S. Hirenzaki and H. Nagahiro [27]. ",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 94,
                    "end": 98,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b26",
                    "text": "[27]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The simulation was carried out with assumption that 3 He plays a role of spectator. ",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 52,
                    "end": 53,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Coupled \u03b7 meson decay on two \u03b3 quanta is assumed to be isotropic in the \u03b7 rest frame and the decay into three \u03c0 0 mesons was simulated assuming uniform phase space population. ",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Each of \u03c0 0 decays into two \u03b3 quanta isotropically in \u03c0 0 rest frame.",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The pd \u2192 3 He\u03b3\u03b3 and pd \u2192 3 He6\u03b3 events identification is based on conditions applied for particle registration time, angles, and kinematic magnitudes such as invariant and missing , 0",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "(201 E Web of Conferences https://doi.org/10.1051/e onf /201919902029 PJ pjc 199 20 9) ",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 81,
                    "end": 83,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b19",
                    "text": "20"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "MESON 2018 29 mass. ",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "For pd \u2192 3 He\u03b3\u03b3 reaction the background processes efficiency was decreased to the level below 0.5% while the bound state decay acceptance is about 10% in the whole beam momentum range (Fig. 1).",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 184,
                    "end": 192,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_0",
                    "text": "(Fig. 1)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In the excess energy region Q3 He\u03b7 < 10 MeV the acceptance for pd \u2192 3 He\u03b7 reaction is neglectable because of small \u03b8 angle for 3 He emission direction. ",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 127,
                    "end": 128,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "This property is useful for searching the bound state near the threshold.",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Actually, the analysis is still in progress. ",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "In case if the bound state is observed, a peak on the excitation curve for both pd \u2192 3 He\u03b3\u03b3 and pd \u2192 3 He6\u03b3 reactions will be obtained.",
            "section": "Searching for a bound state",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
